Trawler window 2026-07-16 to 2026-07-18 (bridging the gap since the last
edition, which was current as of 2026-07-16).

- 6 new feed items across US/EU/ME desks (data, robo, ai, dews)
- III-9 (Golden Dome/SDA sensing-tracking) refreshed: the previously
  provisional Tranche 1 relaunch is now confirmed (21 more York Space
  satellites launched 16 Jul), plus a new Golden Defender missile-range
  instrumentation ship award extending the tracking architecture to sea
- I-5 (allied autonomy force-structure consolidation) gets its first
  concrete capability output — IAI's "Hypnosis" anti-swarm EW system
- III-10 (allied drone/counter-drone mass-production funding) extended
  with Ukraine's reported ~90%-of-targets drone-strike ratio, the
  operational payoff the funding wave is racing to sustain
- One item (SOCOM SOF-peculiar attack drone RFI) and one (DARPA/Northrop
  robotic satellite-servicing spacecraft) left unassigned (serial: null)
  — single-source/not-yet-clustered watch items
- All 21 existing serials bumped age +1; standing China/PLA net-assessment
  serials (I-3, I-6, II-4) carried forward with no fresh in-window item
  this cycle, per the standing-coverage rule
- edition/feedAsOf updated to 2026-07-18

